body.text:
Where do you see yourself in a century?

 

At DIADOZ, we are working to leave a big impact in our little corner of the universe. We give you the bare bones of this website which serves a new chapter. It will serve as the platform for where we can build our creative ideas and dreams. We want this to be a springboard for dope execution and memorable experiences. We were just some kids who strayed far from where they came from and found themselves in the hills of West Virginia. That’s where the story begins, and the rest will be history.

body.text:
DIADOZ.COM

Designed and developed from the ground up we used technology like NodeJS, MongoDB, and Angular 4. We even created an in house Content Management System so no need for WordPress. This allowed us to customize all of the site’s aspects. Our intentions with the architecture of this page is for it to be somewhere creators want to be featured on because it shows off their work in a grand scale. As the platform evolves so will the content. Some of the current features of the site include the following:

The vision with using horizontal scrolling is a nod to the art gallery experience. Moving past the works and checking out the pieces that catch your attention. We call this Gallery Mode.  Soon we want to make inhouse & guest curated galleries to bring a spotlight some the illest works around.
We want to showcase our videos and have them be the center of the page. That’s why we feature them to take up the whole screen.

Inspired by art gallery description cards and Google’s info cards, this feature of the site is really important to us. Here we want to be able to give as much credit to people involved in the making of what we post.

One of the biggest components of the site is music. For now we will rely on other sites as we look for ways to bring the best listening experience on our site.

 

~

 

So with that, we present to you our website. It was built from the ground up by a couple of diadoz coders. This is just the first bare bones iteration of our vision. We plan to have many more in the coming month so keep an eye out!

 

•X•

body.summary: Small-town Pennsylvania artist Lil Skies blossoms through the setbacks of growing up away from the metropolis and maneuvering into mainstream. This is Skies’ first project on all major streaming platforms. On the album you will hear vocals from consistent collaborator, Landon Cube, and producers Cashmoney AP & Menoh Beats. Skies has also collaborated with many artists from West Virginia; Multiple film collaborations with Director, Nick Jandora; Northern Panhandle now LA based Sound Engineer, NeekAttack, has worked on Track No. 11 as well as other songs not on this project; Official Logo designed & developed by multidisciplinary artist, 2FlyTy;  And in-state performance collaborations with disc jockeys DJ Yemi & DJ 2Time.
body.title: Life of a Dark Rose

body.summary: “Spanish rap phenomenon C. Tangana had a massive 2017. His infectious, trap-inspired flip on flamenco, “Mala Mujer,” racked up over 20 million YouTube views, and an all-star remix of the song featured Farruko and French Montana. At a time when trap en español is reaching more ears worldwide than ever, the artist born Antón Álvarez Alfaro has risen to become one of Spain’s biggest artists in the genre.  So, he has reason to celebrate. In a new video for the self-assured “No Te Pegas” — a lurking, minimal song from his 2017 album Ídolo — C. Tangana flexes in front of a motel sign showing his own name in lights, parties with beautiful women in a high-rise hotel, and recruits Peruvian R&B artist A.CHAL to add a narced out new guest verse. Over email, C. Tangana said, "We all know Spanish [music] is bigger than ever, god bless Daddy and José. What comes next is the Latin New Wave. A.CHAL's un duro, it became clear to me since he put out his last mixtape. About the video shoot...Las Vegas is a crazy place, I don't remember half of it." A.CHAL added: “I met C. Tangana in Brooklyn at a showcase and I fucked with the wave he was creating in Spain. The collab came about organically. We linked during Latin Grammy week in Vegas and came together for the video.””  - THE FADER
body.title: No Te Pegas (Feat. A.CHAL)

OG Lil Jit - Revenge of the Clout [Front Cover]
OG Lil Jit - Revenge of the Clout

body.summary: In the trenches of WV, OG Lil Jit along with DIADOZ premieres his new EP titled Revenge of the Clout. The journey in completing this project was a long one and OG Lil Jit was able to gather up a group of talented individuals to release this grandiose EP. The futuristic space theme not only ties in with the art direction and title but also is engraved in each one of the tracks as he flows effortlessly from using melodies and autotuning to being able to switch it up with line after line after line. Jit has been perfecting his craft and every project seems like another push forward. We are excited for OG Lil Jit's future. Keep an eye/ear out!
body.title: Revenge of the Clout
